			<h1>Defining the Problem</h1>	
			<p>Before any design, it was important to understand what we were designing for; what problems were we trying to solve. As an initial step, I led working sessions with our client, conducted literature research, and began asking important questions:
			</p>
			<div class="aside">
				<p class="aside-text">Who are our users? What do they need from a video player? When do they watch videos online? Why do they stop?</p>
			</div>
			<p>I helped pull together our findings into focused user requirements for the project. We used the requirements and research to design out key scenarios for the video player.</p>
